This paper deals with the development of value-aligned agents, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning models, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. The use of natural language processing techniques to classify normative and non-normative situations in the comic strip indicates that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the societal norms encoded in the comic strip, which suggests that cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of value-aligned agents in education, which suggests that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible sub-category as well.
